<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 7:16PM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHERN ANSON...SOUTHWESTERN
MONTGOMERY...NORTHWESTERN RICHMOND AND SOUTHEASTERN STANLY COUNTIES
THROUGH 815 PM EST...
At 715 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Marshville, or 11 miles northwest of Wadesboro,
moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ansonville, Polkton, Norwood, Mount Gilead, Peachland, Uwharrie
Haven, Covington, Pekin, Lake Tillery, and Blewett Falls Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Doppler radar has indicated weak rotation with this storm. If the
storm intensifies and rotation strengthens, a warning may need to be
issued.</instruction>
